      "date": "2013-07-30 10:11:08.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n\"From what I have seen, the agent client served the restore request and copied file back to lustre, then it called copy_end ioctl to send progress REQ back to MDT. However, it was returned with ENOENT when trying to get data_version(this is because ll_data_version() doesn't refresh layout so it used stale layout to send getattr REQ to OFD), then coordinator received this error and refused to release layout.\"\n\nll_data_version() is done on the volatile file, not the file being restored. The volatile file is not locked, is stripped, and information is accurate.\n\nIf data_version is done on the wrong fid, that's the bug.\nBut, what you have changed is BREAKING the code. You could not drop this feature. May be this help for this issue, but this is not the good fix for that. We need to read data_version before sending progress REQ back to coordinator. If you do not do so, you will not be able to release the file after being restored. (try: archive+release+restore+release with this patch).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
